      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCKING WROXTON (2) was in the money two runs ago then was about the mark again last time over 1790m at this track, finishing 4.5 metres from the winner in second. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Tackles a similar assignment and he can take care of this line-up. PUNTO CALIENTE (4) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 6 metres from the winner in third over 1790m here. Good enough to take out a race like this. SNEAKY PHILTRA (1) last appeared when third over 1790m at Ararat seven months ago. Keep an eye out for positive market movement. APOLOGY ACCEPTED (7) disappointed last time but is a chance based on a good second over 2190m at this circuit two runs back. Can bounce back.",
